1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,000
Welcome to Gulim. Click "Start" and proceed with Google Sign-In to authenticate.

2
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:10,000
Select the Google account. This account's spreadsheet will be used as the database.

3
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:17,000
Since the app is currently unverified, click "Advanced" and "Go to gulim.co.kr" to bypass the warning.

4
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:26,000
[Crucial] The app requests spreadsheets scope. This is required to read/write specific cell data using the Google Sheets API.

5
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:34,000
On the welcome screen, use the Google Drive Picker to select the specific investment spreadsheet to link.

6
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:46,000
[Read Operation] The dashboard uses sheets.values.get to read specific cell ranges (assets, returns) from the user's sheet.

7
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:52,000
[Write Operation] Moving to the History tab to demonstrate writing data. We will add a new dividend record.

8
00:00:52,000 --> 00:01:01,000
Enter stock info and amount. When "Save" is clicked, the app prepares a sheets.values.append request.

9
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:19,000
[Verification] The new row is successfully appended to the specific sheet. This granular cell-level update requires the spreadsheets scope.

10
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:30,000
In Settings, users can change the linked file ID. The app only accesses the specific spreadsheet selected here.


